OL,3,CBrothers sentenced over #3.2m tax scam
OL,5,FIt mean the brothers should have paid
OL,6,F#3.2million in tax, but they failed to
OL,7,Fdeclare their revenue to HMRC and used
OL,8,Ftheir offshore businesses to hide the
OL,9,Fprofits.
OL,11,FWhen HMRC began make enquiries, both
OL,12,Fmen were given a chance to declare any
OL,13,Ftax liability, but failed to
OL,14,Facknowledge any association with their
OL,15,Foffshore companies.
OL,17,FZoe Gascoyne, deputy director of fraud
OL,18,Finvestigation at HMRC, said the Hirsts
OL,19,Fhad "numerous opportunities" to be
OL,20,Fhonest about their tax affairs.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G4/5
